A veteran Yoruba actor, John Adewumi known as ‘Baba Tafa Oloyede’ is dead. The General Secretary of Theater Arts and Motion Picture Producers Association of Nigeria (TAMPAN), Osun State, Mr Ademola Oyedokun confirmed the death of the veteran actor to The Nation. Oyedokun promised to make the detail of his demise available later.   Binance probes 281 Nigerian cryptocurrency accounts     MC Oluomo qualifies to be Oshodi monarch, says Royal family…     Presidency: Nobody can undermine Southern interest in PDP,…   Tafa Oloyede started his career in 1974 under the tutelage of the late Oyin Adejobi. - Advertisement - He featured in many movies that include: ‘Jaiyesimi’, ‘Ayanmo’, ‘Ekuro Oloja’, ‘Orogun’, ‘Akanji Oniposi’ that made him popular and others.